comment: Lowry (TOR) makes contact with Teague's (ATL) head that affects his driving shot attempt.
Powell (TOR) sets the screen on Sefolosha (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Valanciunas (TOR) firms up as he sets the screen on Sefolosha (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Sefolosha (ATL) makes incidental contact with DeRozan (TOR) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Horford (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position as he contests DeRozan's (TOR) driving shot attempt.
Sefolosha (ATL) clamps the arm and leg of Valanciunas (TOR), affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Sefolosha (ATL) sets the screen on Valanciunas (TOR) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Joseph (TOR) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Teague (ATL) that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Millsap (ATL) runs through the legal screen set by Lowry (TOR).
Horford (ATL) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with DeRozan (TOR) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.

After communicating with the Replay Center, there was no conclusive video evidence to overturn the ruling on the court that the ball was touched simultaneously prior to going OOB. The ruling on the court of a jump ball would stand.
Horford (ATL) grabs Valanciunas (TOR) and affects his FOM and ability to set the screen.
Powell (TOR) commits a take foul on Millsap (ATL).
Horford (ATL) legally contests Lowry's (TOR) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
DeRozan (TOR) commits a take foul on Teague (ATL).
